775
00:43:44.302 --> 00:43:46.242
inhibitor of phosphofructokinase.

776
00:43:46.542 --> 00:43:50.282
So when you don't just keep the carbon in the mitochondria, you also

777
00:43:50.322 --> 00:43:53.382
prevent its negative feedback for the rest of things.

778
00:43:53.422 --> 00:43:56.892
So all in all, these cells were much better, were

779
00:43:57.502 --> 00:44:01.262
metabolically superior to typical

780
00:44:01.582 --> 00:44:02.022
T cells.

781
00:44:03.182 --> 00:44:05.062
So what did that mean when we put them in vitro?

